iii) for the fourth PING request (P4) received from the UE following the third PING request received from the UE, estimating a third delay timer (Delay Timer#3) corresponding to the anticipated occurrence of the next PING request, a third proactive allocation window being started at the end of Delay Timer#3, wherein Delay Timer#3 = ((XI + X2 + X3) - X4), X1=Received_SFN#P2/Subframe_Num#P2âˆ’Received_SFN#P1/Subframe_Num#P1, X2 equals PROACTIVE_ALLOCATION_GAP_Win#1 if proactive-allocation-data-received-index equals 1, otherwise X2 equals zero, X3=Start Delay Offsetproactiveâˆ’allocationâˆ’dataâˆ’receivedâˆ’indexâˆ’proactiveâˆ’allocationâˆ’windowâˆ’startâˆ’index, X4=Current_SFN#P4/Subframe_Num#P4âˆ’Received_SFN#P4/Subframe_Num#P4;
wherein SFN represents system frame number, Subframe_Num represents subframe number, UEAppToMACLayerDelay represents delay from the PING application (App) to the MAC Layer in the UE, and SR represents scheduling request.
